15:01.944 --> 15:03.903
You keep your
eye on that door.

15:05.034 --> 15:13.042
[squeaking]

15:21.485 --> 15:26.795
HAROLD:
Hey, what the hell are you doing
coming through the front?

15:26.882 --> 15:28.928
You trying to put us
both out of business?

15:29.015 --> 15:32.279
WOMAN:
I'm done
working for tonight.

15:32.366 --> 15:34.759
I was just hoping to rest.

15:35.760 --> 15:37.240
HAROLD:
[sighs]

15:37.327 --> 15:38.720
I'm sorry.

15:38.807 --> 15:40.374
I didn't mean to
raise my voice.

15:40.461 --> 15:44.421
But we all gotta be careful.

15:44.508 --> 15:48.599
That ol' Baskan's been coming
down hard on folks lately.

15:48.686 --> 15:56.694
♪ [suspenseful music]

16:01.221 --> 16:03.136
MAN:
Why not be a man
who dreams for himself?

16:03.223 --> 16:10.099
[♪♪♪]

16:10.186 --> 16:13.537
MAN:
Hey, [indistinct]
a welder and apprentice?

16:13.624 --> 16:14.712
Come on!

16:14.799 --> 16:16.062
[indistinct]

16:16.149 --> 16:22.198
[footsteps]

16:22.285 --> 16:30.250
♪ [morose music] ♪

16:30.337 --> 16:32.208
[door squeaks]

16:50.748 --> 16:56.406
[♪♪♪]

16:56.493 --> 16:58.321
DONNIE:
Mom.

16:58.408 --> 17:01.107
[knocking]

17:01.194 --> 17:03.152
Mom.

17:04.066 --> 17:05.936
Mom--.

17:06.025 --> 17:09.854
Oh, damnation, Donnie, I
thought you were an outsider.

17:09.941 --> 17:12.117
Are you trying to forfeit
your visitation privileges?

17:12.204 --> 17:13.597
DONNIE:
What the
hell is this thing?

17:13.684 --> 17:14.990
WOMAN:
It keeps her
body heat regulated.

17:15.077 --> 17:16.383
DONNIE:
Shouldn't she be awake by now?

17:16.470 --> 17:18.124
WOMAN:
Hard to say.

17:18.211 --> 17:20.691
