the chaos around her.

17:49.198 --> 17:52.941
[♪♪♪]

17:53.028 --> 18:01.080
[indistinct radio chatter]

18:07.260 --> 18:11.655
MAN:
--this trying year of
1959, to you, Mr. Bascum.

18:11.742 --> 18:13.831
[door chimes]

18:13.918 --> 18:15.442
WOMAN:
Two platters?

18:15.529 --> 18:16.747
Double meat?

18:16.834 --> 18:22.536
BRENTON:
Thanks, Miss Sheri.

18:22.623 --> 18:25.539
SHERI:
You boys catch Father
Coughlin's morning program?

18:25.626 --> 18:28.194
BRENTON:
No, we don't
get a signal at the coop.

18:28.281 --> 18:31.022
SHERI:
I hate saying this, but
I think it's safe to say their

18:31.110 --> 18:33.024
finger's creeping
towards that button.

18:33.112 --> 18:36.550
BRENTON:
Oh, well wouldn't
that be something.

18:36.637 --> 18:38.204
SHERI:
Well if it's gonna
happen to any civilization

18:38.291 --> 18:40.597
it'd be this one.

18:40.684 --> 18:44.862
We truly are living
in a carnival of wickedness.

18:44.949 --> 18:48.257
BRENTON:
Well, we won't
stay aloof to the danger.

18:48.344 --> 18:50.564
We sure are grateful you're
here to help keep us informed.

18:50.651 --> 18:53.567
Aren't we, Donnie?

18:53.654 --> 18:55.743
DONNIE:
I got other concerns.

18:55.830 --> 18:57.179
